attributes.description: standard with a 4-year/120 000 km warranty, 4-year/unlimited km roadside assistance and 5-year/unlimited km corrosion warranty. A 4-year/60 000 km service plan, however, is an extra-cost option. The recommended service interval is 15 000 km or every 12 months, whichever occurs first. 6.3 L/100 km for the EcoSport 1.0T Active. With its slightly softer suspension setup, which I think is perfect for this type of vehicle, the Ford deals with most road imperfections (bumps and potholes) with minimal intrusion into the cabin. It has a quiet and comfortable ride at city speeds, and although we didn’t do much open-road driving, I can’t imagine it would fare differently at highway speeds. It offers a mature and refined on-road demeanour that befits its price point.
